Sales Forecasting — Time Series Analysis
Tech Stack: Python, Pandas, Statsmodels, XGBoost, Matplotlib

- Engineered a complete end-to-end time series forecasting pipeline 
  on 4 years of Superstore retail data (9,994 transactions)

- Performed data preprocessing including datetime conversion, 
  missing value imputation for 220 missing dates, and outlier 
  capping using 99th percentile winsorization

- Conducted EDA revealing strong weekly seasonality and 
  Year-over-Year upward sales trend using ACF/PACF analysis

- Built SARIMA(1,1,1)(1,1,1,7) model achieving MAE of 1857, 
  successfully capturing weekly seasonal patterns

- Developed XGBoost model with 12 engineered lag features 
  (lag_1 to lag_30, rolling averages) achieving comparable 
  MAE of 1898 with superior spike-tracking behavior

- Generated 30-day future sales forecast to support inventory 
  planning and budget allocation decisions
